<br>
Part of the reason I don't think they want to mess with the level cap is the absurd system they use on the planes, where monsters are grossly underconned and thus would fall within the realm of Disintegrate.  Now, the obvious answer to this is to raise the 'level' of the monsters so they CON more rationally, but Verant likes their uneven consider level of creatures so much they barely even bother to defend the way its implemented. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swipey>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/02 7:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> &quot;I can see why you'd be outraged and filled with contempt for the idea (rolling eyes). &quot;<br>
<br>
Thats the part that prompted me to ask if you were trolling.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I mean, gimme a break.  How many threads are there on this very board where Wizards are outraged and filled with contempt about what they feel are their class defining abilities getting farmed out to other classes? <br>
<br>
How many Wizards are outraged and filled with contempt about ANYONE else getting nukes that even approach Wizard nukes?  Look in the Polls section and you'll see one about giving TLs to druids, in which over half the respondents reply in the maximum negative to the idea.<br>
<br>
If you don't understand why someone might possibly get a tad outraged at a suggestion to farm out their class abilities to others, then you're either truly obtuse, or you are being intentionally obtuse in order to get a rise out of people.  And since I don't think you're truly obtuse, I'm supposing you're some kind of troll, at least in this thread. <br>
<br>
<br>
What you proposed was 90 pick skill for a 20 wizard.  90 pick is what a 17 rogue can get, so you're proposing to give wizards a rogue ability at -3 levels, but with NO need to practice it, or carry/equip picks. <br>
<br>
Is it outrageous or contemptible, then, to turn the tables and suggest giving access to certain wizard spells to other classes, but only when they are 3 levels higher than a wizard needs to be to cast them?  And to not require some of the hassles required of the wizard to cast the same spells?<br>
<br>
The knock spell you suggest is straight out of D&amp;D, so I will suggest another ability from D&amp;D :<br>
<br>
Rogues can cast spells from scrolls.  It would take a skill check (skill raises like any other trade/rogue skill, ie with use or training), but no mana, and would consume the scroll when attempted. Oh, and the rogue would simply HAVE to be at least 3 levels higher than the level of the spell.<br>
<br>
It would take a 52 rogue to cast Ice Comet (49) off an Ice Comet scroll, or a 22 Rogue to TL someone to Nexus.<br>
<br>
The balance factor is the fail chance (as much as 5% if skill is maxed, more if it isnt) and the fact that the scroll, often costing -several- pp from a vendor, is destroyed, succeed or fail.<br>
<br>
<br>
How about it?  Outrageous and Contemptible?  Does it offend you that I would even suggest such a thing?  Be honest now...<br>
