<br>
The point of the previous suggestion was not to start a debate about exactly what would be a &quot;fair equivalent&quot;, but to illustrate a case of one's class abilities being given to other classes that would hit closer to home for (and not benefit) Wizards.  <br>
<br>
Wizards seem to be VERY concerned with their nukes, deeming that they should not only be larger, but also be more mana efficient than any other classes nukes.  Being &quot;Masters of Arcane Direct Damage&quot; is what they hold as their &quot;class defining&quot; ability.<br>
<br>
Most old rogues I know never asked to be &quot;masters of situational melee damage&quot;, though.  They made rogues not so they could do L337 damage while grouped, but instead they made them so they could creep around, get into places others could not (despite traps or locks!) and steal stuff.  Verant, though, never seems to have paid much attention to that motivation.  There are what? less than 10 locked doors in the entire world (some of which lead nowhere), still fewer traps (some of which are not disarmable), and actually stealing anything is a no-no.  But still, the skills associated with this vision of what a rogue is are considered &quot;class defining&quot; by a lot of rogues.<br>
<br>
After someone gets a &quot;knock&quot; spell, they may well start lobbying for a &quot;detect traps&quot; one, a &quot;super Invisibility&quot; that is as hard to see as sneak/hide, and maybe even a &quot;filch&quot; spell that simulates Pickpocket (But don't worry rogues!  Its 3 whole levels less than your Pick Pocket, and costs an eensy bit of mana!)<br>
<br>
<br>
So you say its nothing to get screaming about, but I say it is, because if it gets done, it establishes a precedent of farming out even the few, weak, rogue class defining abilities to other classes via spellcraft.<br>
<br>
It just seems funny to me how willing some people are to farm out OTHER classes class defining abilities while simultaneously guarding their own class defining abilities very very jealously.<br>
<br>
Is that a little morte clear to YOU?  (Rolls eyes)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
