I dont know how I'd split up Religious stuff.  Maybe Blessings (buffs), Wrath (attacks) and Healing (heals, duh!)  Maybe? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 6217<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/24/02 11:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Religious stuff would either have to be based on general ethos (good, evil) or on the 'deity' worshipped, so you would have different kinds of spells available to you based on your deity.  Religious could actually be pretty regimented simply because they are part of an organized religion.  An alternative would be simply to have healers, and leave the religious stuff out entirely - it does make some people pretty uncomfortable and you can have the same feel to the game without it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 9851<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/25/02 4:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Hmmm. I actually sent in a different version of a knock spell in a request from the Developer's Corner. I got back an e-mail saying what a good idea it was, and that it might make it to Test after Luclin. At which point, of course, said spell guy was gone.<br>
<br>
My thoughts when I sent it in: There aren't enough locked doors in EQ. Not only is it implausible (&quot;come on down and BUST RIGHT INTO MY LAIR!&quot;), it devalues rogues being something other than backstabbers. If you wanted a lot more locked doors in the game, you'd also want everyone NOT to be held captive to one class. (Brell knows we get enough of that as is.) So give wizards a Knock spell that would unlock, say, bard-unlockable doors, and maybe with an upgrade to let them unlock, say, 200 level doors too.<br>
<br>
I like Grim's idea of pegging the level to higher than an equivalent rogue's skill (well, it's essentially the same idea, just facing the other way).<br>
<br>
I'd also have a mage-summoned Skeleton Key line that worked the same way. (No drop, probably.)<br>
<br>
Of course, if VI did this, it would HAVE to go hand-in-hand with tossing in lots more locked doors, including in old world content. Anything else wouldn't be fair.<br>
<br>
(And, for the record, the firepot room, the Nexus and PoK represents a much bigger daily hit on wizards' secondary abilities than a Knock spell ever could. Unclench.) <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz_toon.gif" height="104" width="390" alt="stats" border=0></a>
