for the most part, all skills are available to all people of all classes (with VERY few exceptions, like only theives can backstab, only barbarians (the warriors of DR) get  combat disiplins (called dances), ect )<br>
<br>
but the learnign rate and effictivness is  different for all classes<br>
all skills are divided into types:<br>
ARMOR, WEAPON, MAGIC, LORE, SURVIVAL<br>
<br>
things like swimming and climbing would be in survivial<br>
carving and other 'tinkering' and music type skills are lore<br>
armor, weapons, and magic are self explanitory<br>
<br>
like moon mages (closest to wizard) are:<br>
primary: magic<br>
secondary: survival, lore<br>
terteriry: survival, weapon<br>
<br>
while a ranger would be<br>
primary survival<br>
secondary lore magic<br>
tert weapon armor<br>
<br>
and my favorite, warrior mages (imagine the nukage of a mage and the fighting ability of a ranger and the defense abilities of a shaman, while it may sound over powered it isn't because of serious evasion and armor penalties)<br>
primary magic <br>
secondary weapon lore<br>
tert survival armour<br>
<br>
skill system rocks, its text based though<br>
<br>
characters are SO different, there are many weapons types, and you gain skill individually<br>
<br>
and its exact oposite of EQ in the skill system, <br>
<br>
there are no level caps on skills, insteead of getting general XP to get levels, you get so many skill ranks in certian skills (depending on your class) then you get a general level<br>
